{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PWqbSMYBSKa1iL8X3eH5y5","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# platform\n2\t\n3\tPurpose: Binary entry point that wires together the metrics and IAM internal packages and serves each on a dedicated port.\n4\t\n5\tTags: main\n6\t\n7\t## Overview\n8\t\n9\tThe `platform` binary is the single runnable entry point for the monolith. It starts the metrics HTTP service on `:8081` and the IAM HTTP service on `:8082`, running them concurrently in the same process.\n10\t\n11\t## File Index\n12\t\n13\t| File | Description | Doc |\n14\t|------|-------------|-----|\n15\t| `main.go` | Instantiates handlers and starts both HTTP servers | [main.go.md](main.go.md) |\n16\t\n17\t## Notes\n18\t\n19\tThe metrics server is launched in a background goroutine; the IAM server blocks the main goroutine. A fatal error from either server (e.g. port already in use) will terminate the entire process via `log.Fatalf`. There is no graceful shutdown mechanism.\n20\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"70c03b5c-a214-4ae0-8a5a-e73f76e974f8","uuid":"1ea7a49d-e120-453a-8144-8588ea0b8ecc","timestamp":"2026-04-05T22:26:35.269Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/establish-regression-recordings/sandbox/regressions/doc-platform-monolith/output/cmd/platform/README.md","content":"# platform\n\nPurpose: Binary entry point that wires together the metrics and IAM internal packages and serves each on a dedicated port.\n\nTags: main\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `platform` binary is the single runnable entry point for the monolith. It starts the metrics HTTP service on `:8081` and the IAM HTTP service on `:8082`, running them concurrently in the same process.\n\n## File Index\n\n| File | Description | Doc |\n|------|-------------|-----|\n| `main.go` | Instantiates handlers and starts both HTTP servers | [main.go.md](main.go.md) |\n\n## Notes\n\nThe metrics server is launched in a background goroutine; the IAM server blocks the main goroutine. A fatal error from either server (e.g. port already in use) will terminate the entire process via `log.Fatalf`. There is no graceful shutdown mechanism.\n","numLines":20,"startLine":1,"totalLines":20}}}
